      "writtenOn": "2026-03-17T21:23:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think you can avoid this fallback by calling this first, with `-q`. If it fails with exit code 1 (catch `GitCommandError`), then it\u0027s not a symbolic ref and it\u0027s a detached HEAD, so run and return the rev_parse from line 3921. Otherwise it\u0027s some other fatal issue and you should throw the exception below.\n\n```\ntry:\n    return self.symbolic_ref(\"-q\", HEAD)\nexcept GitCommandError as e:\n    if e.git_rc \u003d\u003d 1:\n        # Detached HEAD. Return the commit SHA instead.\n        return self.rev_parse(HEAD)\n    raise NoManifestException(self.GetDotgitPath(HEAD), str(e))\n```",
      "revId": "a3287bb82c0a2a3417f1ab5f8f9188d3460f55e6",
